407    /**
408     * Update post content with image placeholders after images are processed
409     *
410     * @since 1.0.0
411     * @param int $post_id Post ID
412     * @return void
413     */
414    private function update_post_content_with_images($post_id) {
415        $post_content = get_post_field('post_content', $post_id);
416        
417        // Get all image URLs for this post
418        $image_urls = $this->get_listing_image_urls($post_id);
419        
420        // Replace universal image placeholders
421        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- LISTING_IMAGES_PLACEHOLDER -->', implode(',', $image_urls), $post_content);
422        
423        // Replace base64 encoded image URLs (for Visual Composer compatibility)
424        $base64_images = $this->get_base64_encoded_images($image_urls);
425        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- BASE64IMAGES_PLACEHOLDER -->', $base64_images, $post_content);
426        
427        // Replace individual image placeholders (1-10)
428        for ($i = 1; $i <= 10; $i++) {
429            $image_url = isset($image_urls[$i - 1]) ? $image_urls[$i - 1] : '';
430            $post_content = str_replace("<!-- LISTING_IMAGE_{$i}_PLACEHOLDER -->", $image_url, $post_content);
431        }
432        
433        // Replace WordPress native placeholders
434        $featured_image_html = $this->get_featured_image_html($post_id);
435        $gallery_html = $this->get_image_gallery_html($post_id);
436        
437        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- FEATURED_IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER -->', $featured_image_html, $post_content);
438        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- IMAGE_GALLERY_PLACEHOLDER -->', $gallery_html, $post_content);
439        
440        
441        // Update the post content
442        wp_update_post(array(
443            'ID' => $post_id,
444            'post_content' => $post_content
445        ));
446    }

631    /**
632     * Sanitize meta value based on data type
633     *
634     * @since 1.2.0
635     * @param mixed $value Raw value from API
636     * @param string $type Sanitization type
637     * @return mixed Sanitized value
638     */
639    private function sanitize_meta_value($value, $type) {
640        if ($value === null || $value === '') {
641            return '';
642        }
643        
644        switch ($type) {
645            case 'text':
646                return sanitize_text_field($value);
647                
648            case 'textarea':
649                return sanitize_textarea_field($value);
650                
651            case 'url':
652                return esc_url_raw($value);
653                
654            case 'int':
655                return intval($value);
656                
657            case 'float':
658                return floatval($value);
659                
660            case 'boolean':
661                // Handle various boolean representations from API
662                if (is_bool($value)) {
663                    return $value ? '1' : '0';
664                }
665                $value = strtolower(trim($value));
666                return in_array($value, array('true', '1', 'yes', 'y'), true) ? '1' : '0';
667                
668            case 'datetime':
669                // Ensure datetime is in MySQL format
670                $timestamp = strtotime($value);
671                return $timestamp ? gmdate('Y-m-d H:i:s', $timestamp) : '';
672                
673            default:
674                return sanitize_text_field($value);

686    private function store_geocoded_coordinates($post_id, $listing) {

695            ));

712                'latitude' => $coordinates['lat'],
713                'longitude' => $coordinates['lng']
714            ));
715        } else {
716            // Store default Toronto coordinates so maps still work
717            update_post_meta($post_id, 'shift8_treb_latitude', 43.6532);
718            update_post_meta($post_id, 'shift8_treb_longitude', -79.3832);
719            
720            shift8_treb_log('Geocoding failed, stored default Toronto coordinates', array(
721                'mls_number' => esc_html($listing['ListingKey']),
722                'address' => esc_html($address),
723                'latitude' => 43.6532,
724                'longitude' => -79.3832
725            ));
726        }

729    /**
730     * Calculate price per square foot
731     *
732     * @since 1.2.0
733     * @param array $listing Listing data
734     * @return float Price per square foot or 0 if cannot calculate
735     */
736    private function calculate_price_per_sqft($listing) {
737        $price = isset($listing['ListPrice']) ? floatval($listing['ListPrice']) : 0;
738        $sqft = isset($listing['LivingArea']) ? floatval($listing['LivingArea']) : 0;
739

742        }
743        
744        return 0;
745    }

747    /**
748     * Calculate days on market
749     *
750     * @since 1.2.0
751     * @param array $listing Listing data
752     * @return int Days on market or 0 if cannot calculate
753     */
754    private function calculate_days_on_market($listing) {
755        $on_market_date = isset($listing['OnMarketDate']) ? $listing['OnMarketDate'] : 
756                         (isset($listing['ListingContractDate']) ? $listing['ListingContractDate'] : '');
757        
758        if (empty($on_market_date)) {
759            return 0;
760        }
761        
762        $market_timestamp = strtotime($on_market_date);
763        if (!$market_timestamp) {
764            return 0;
765        }
766        
767        return max(0, floor((time() - $market_timestamp) / (24 * 60 * 60)));
768    }

818    /**
819     * Process listing images using AMPRE Media API
820     * 
821     * Best Practice: Single-process import for atomic operations and immediate user experience
822     *
823     * @since 1.0.0
824     * @param int $post_id Post ID
825     * @param array $listing Listing data
826     * @return array Statistics about image processing
827     */
828    private function process_listing_images($post_id, $listing) {
829        $mls_number = sanitize_text_field($listing['ListingKey']);
830        $stats = array(
831            'total' => 0,
832            'downloaded' => 0,
833            'failed' => 0,
834            'featured_set' => false
835        );
836        
837        // Get media from AMPRE API
838        if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
839            WP_CLI::line("  Fetching media for MLS {$mls_number}...");
840        }
841        
842        require_once SHIFT8_TREB_PLUGIN_DIR . 'includes/class-shift8-treb-ampre-service.php';
843        $ampre_service = new Shift8_TREB_AMPRE_Service($this->settings);
844        
845        $media_items = $ampre_service->get_media_for_listing($mls_number);
846        
847        if (is_wp_error($media_items) || empty($media_items)) {
848            if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
849                WP_CLI::line("  No media found for MLS {$mls_number}");
850            }
851            shift8_treb_log('No media found for listing', array(
852                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
853                'error' => is_wp_error($media_items) ? $media_items->get_error_message() : 'No media items'
854            ));
855            return $stats;
856        }
857
858        $stats['total'] = count($media_items);
859        
860        if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
861            WP_CLI::line("  Found {$stats['total']} images for MLS {$mls_number}");
862        }
863        
864        shift8_treb_log('Processing listing images', array(
865            'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
866            'image_count' => $stats['total']
867        ));
868
869        $featured_image_set = false;
870        $preferred_image_id = null;
871        $first_successful_image = null;
872
873        // Performance: Allow unlimited images by default, but provide filter for hosting constraints
874        // Following .cursorrules performanceOptimizationPatterns: make expensive operations conditional
875        $original_count = count($media_items);
876        $max_images = apply_filters('shift8_treb_max_images_per_listing', 0); // 0 = unlimited
877        if ($max_images > 0) {
878            $media_items = array_slice($media_items, 0, $max_images);
879            shift8_treb_log('Limited images per listing', array(
880                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
881                'original_count' => $original_count,
882                'limited_count' => count($media_items),
883                'max_images' => $max_images
884            ));
885        }
886
887        // Performance: Check processing mode
888        // Following .cursorrules performanceOptimizationPatterns: batch processing default for better performance
889        $skip_images = isset($this->settings['skip_image_download']) && $this->settings['skip_image_download'];
890        $batch_mode = !isset($this->settings['batch_image_processing']) || $this->settings['batch_image_processing']; // Default: true
891        
892        if ($skip_images) {
893            shift8_treb_log('Skipping image download for fast sync', array(
894                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
895            ));
896            
897            // Store external references only
898            foreach ($media_items as $index => $media) {
899                if (isset($media['MediaURL']) && !empty($media['MediaURL'])) {
900                    $is_preferred = isset($media['PreferredPhotoYN']) && $media['PreferredPhotoYN'] === true;
901                    $this->store_external_image_reference($post_id, $media['MediaURL'], $mls_number, $index + 1, $is_preferred);
902                }
903            }
904            return $stats;
905        }
906
907        // Batch processing mode for better performance
908        if ($batch_mode) {
909            if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
910                WP_CLI::line("  Starting batch download for MLS {$mls_number}...");
911            }
912            return $this->process_images_batch($post_id, $media_items, $mls_number, $stats);
913        }
914
915        foreach ($media_items as $index => $media) {
916            if (!isset($media['MediaURL']) || empty($media['MediaURL'])) {
917                continue;
918            }
919
920            $image_url = esc_url_raw($media['MediaURL']);
921            $is_preferred = isset($media['PreferredPhotoYN']) && $media['PreferredPhotoYN'] === true;
922            
923            // Best Practice: Download with retry and fallback to external URL
924            $attachment_id = $this->download_and_attach_image_with_retry($image_url, $post_id, $mls_number, $index + 1);
925
926            if ($attachment_id) {
927                $stats['downloaded']++;
928                
929                // Track first successful image as fallback
930                if (!$first_successful_image) {
931                    $first_successful_image = $attachment_id;
932                }
933                
934                // Track preferred image for featured image (highest priority)
935                if ($is_preferred) {
936                    $preferred_image_id = $attachment_id;
937                }
938            } else {
939                $stats['failed']++;
940                
941                // Fallback: Store external URL for future retry or display
942                $this->store_external_image_reference($post_id, $image_url, $mls_number, $index + 1, $is_preferred);
943                
944                shift8_treb_log('Image download failed, stored external reference', array(
945                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
946                    'image_url' => esc_html($image_url),
947                    'index' => $index
948                ));
949            }
950        }
951
952        // Featured image priority logic:
953        // 1. First image (image_number = 1) - ALWAYS gets priority for consistency
954        // 2. Preferred image (PreferredPhotoYN = true) - secondary priority
955        // 3. First successfully downloaded image - fallback
956        
957        // Find the first image (image_number = 1) if it was successfully downloaded
958        $first_image_id = null;
959        foreach ($media_items as $index => $media) {
960            if (($index + 1) == 1) { // First image
961                $existing_attachment = $this->get_existing_attachment($mls_number, 1);
962                if ($existing_attachment) {
963                    $first_image_id = $existing_attachment;
964                } elseif ($first_successful_image && ($index + 1) == 1) {
965                    $first_image_id = $first_successful_image;
966                }
967                break;
968            }
969        }
970        
971        // Set featured image with priority: First image > Preferred > First successful
972        $featured_image_id = $first_image_id ?: ($preferred_image_id ?: $first_successful_image);
973        
974        if ($featured_image_id) {
975            set_post_thumbnail($post_id, $featured_image_id);
976            $stats['featured_set'] = true;
977            
978            $priority_type = $first_image_id ? 'first_image' : ($preferred_image_id ? 'preferred' : 'first_successful');
979            
980            shift8_treb_log('Set featured image', array(
981                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
982                'attachment_id' => $featured_image_id,
983                'priority_type' => $priority_type
984            ));
985        }
986
987        // Log final statistics
988        shift8_treb_log('Image processing completed', array(
989            'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
990            'stats' => $stats
991        ));
992
993        return $stats;
994    }

996    /**
997     * Download and attach image to post with enhanced error handling
998     * 
999     * Best Practice: Robust download with proper validation and cleanup
1000     *
1001     * @since 1.0.0
1002     * @param string $image_url Image URL
1003     * @param int $post_id Post ID
1004     * @param string $mls_number MLS number
1005     * @param int $image_number Image number
1006     * @return int|false Attachment ID on success, false on failure
1007     */
1008    private function download_and_attach_image($image_url, $post_id, $mls_number, $image_number) {
1009        try {
1010            // Best Practice: Validate URL before attempting download
1011            if (!filter_var($image_url, FILTER_VALIDATE_URL)) {
1012                shift8_treb_log('Invalid image URL', array(
1013                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
1014                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
1015                ));
1016                return false;
1017            }
1018
1019            // Best Practice: Check if image already exists to avoid duplicates
1020            $existing_attachment = $this->get_existing_attachment($mls_number, $image_number);
1021            if ($existing_attachment) {
1022                return $existing_attachment;
1023            }
1024
1025            // Performance: Optimized download settings with faster timeout
1026            $response = wp_remote_get($image_url, array(
1027                'timeout' => 10, // Reduced from 30 to 10 seconds
1028                'user-agent' => 'WordPress/TREB-Plugin',
1029                'headers' => array(
1030                    'Accept' => 'image/*'
1031                ),
1032                'sslverify' => false // Skip SSL verification for speed (external images)
1033            ));
1034            
1035            if (is_wp_error($response)) {
1036                shift8_treb_log('Image download failed', array(
1037                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
1038                    'error' => $response->get_error_message(),
1039                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
1040                ));
1041                return false;
1042            }
1043
1044            $response_code = wp_remote_retrieve_response_code($response);
1045            if ($response_code !== 200) {
1046                shift8_treb_log('Image download HTTP error', array(
1047                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
1048                    'response_code' => $response_code,
1049                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
1050                ));
1051                return false;
1052            }
1053
1054            $image_data = wp_remote_retrieve_body($response);
1055            if (empty($image_data)) {
1056                return false;
1057            }
1058
1059            // Best Practice: Validate image data
1060            $image_size = strlen($image_data);
1061            if ($image_size < 1024) { // Less than 1KB is likely not a valid image
1062                shift8_treb_log('Image too small', array(
1063                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
1064                    'size' => $image_size,
1065                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
1066                ));
1067                return false;
1068            }
1069
1070            // Best Practice: Determine file extension from content type
1071            $content_type = wp_remote_retrieve_header($response, 'content-type');
1072            $extension = $this->get_file_extension_from_content_type($content_type);
1073            
1074            // Prepare filename with proper extension
1075            $filename = sanitize_file_name($mls_number . '_' . $image_number . '.' . $extension);
1076            
1077            // Upload to WordPress media library
1078            $upload = wp_upload_bits($filename, null, $image_data);
1079            
1080            if ($upload['error']) {
1081                shift8_treb_log('WordPress upload failed', array(
1082                    'error' => $upload['error'],
1083                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
1084                    'filename' => esc_html($filename)
1085                ));
1086                return false;
1087            }
1088
1089            // Create attachment with proper metadata
1090            $attachment = array(
1091                'post_mime_type' => $content_type ?: 'image/jpeg',
1092                'post_title' => sanitize_text_field($mls_number . ' - Photo ' . $image_number),
1093                'post_content' => '',
1094                'post_status' => 'inherit',
1095                'post_excerpt' => sanitize_text_field('Property photo for MLS ' . $mls_number)
1096            );
1097
1098            $attachment_id = wp_insert_attachment($attachment, $upload['file'], $post_id);
1099
1100            if (is_wp_error($attachment_id)) {
1101                // Clean up uploaded file if attachment creation fails
1102                if (file_exists($upload['file'])) {
1103                    wp_delete_file($upload['file']);
1104                }
1105                shift8_treb_log('Attachment creation failed', array(
1106                    'error' => esc_html($attachment_id->get_error_message()),
1107                    'post_id' => $post_id,
1108                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
1109                    'image_number' => $image_number
1110                ), 'error');
1111                return false;
1112            }
1113
1114            // Verify post_parent was set correctly (debugging for post_parent issue)
1115            $created_attachment = get_post($attachment_id);
1116            if ($created_attachment && $created_attachment->post_parent != $post_id) {
1117                shift8_treb_log('Post parent mismatch detected', array(
1118                    'attachment_id' => $attachment_id,
1119                    'expected_parent' => $post_id,
1120                    'actual_parent' => $created_attachment->post_parent,
1121                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
1122                    'image_number' => $image_number
1123                ), 'warning');
1124                
1125                // Attempt to fix the post_parent
1126                wp_update_post(array(

1992    /**

1994     *
1995     * @since 1.0.0
1996     * @param string $address Full address string
1997     * @return array Address components
1998     */
1999    private function parse_address($address) {
2000        $parts = array(
2001            'number' => '',
2002            'street' => '',
2003            'unit' => ''
2004        );
2005
2006        if (empty($address)) {
2007            return $parts;
2008        }
2009
2010        // Basic address parsing - can be enhanced later
2011        $address = trim($address);
2012        
2013        // Extract unit number (look for patterns like "Unit 123", "Apt 456", "#789")
2014        if (preg_match('/(?:Unit|Apt|Suite|#)\s*([A-Za-z0-9]+)/i', $address, $matches)) {
2015            $parts['unit'] = $matches[1];
2016            $address = preg_replace('/(?:Unit|Apt|Suite|#)\s*[A-Za-z0-9]+/i', '', $address);
2017        }
2018
2019        // Extract street number (first number in the address)
2020        if (preg_match('/^(\d+)/', trim($address), $matches)) {
2021            $parts['number'] = $matches[1];
2022            $address = preg_replace('/^\d+\s*/', '', $address);
2023        }
2024
2025        // Remaining is street name (clean up extra spaces and commas)
2026        $parts['street'] = trim(preg_replace('/,.*$/', '', $address));
2027
2028        return $parts;
2029    }
